Description: Snake, going to right; illustration to Denon's 'Voyage dans la Basse et la Haute Egypte' (Paris, 1802), volume I, plate 104. c.1799/1802 Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Baron Dominique Vivant Denon
Curator's comments: Engraved for Denon's 'Voyage dans la Basse et la Haute Egypte' (Paris, 1802), written during his journey into Egypt (1798-99) and illustrated by plates engraved by various artists (Denon, Baltard, Gallien, Malbeste, Coiny...) after Denon's drawings. The British Museum keeps the majority of these drawings.
